Spokesman of Foreign Ministry Lambastes Joint Military Exercises 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry gave the following answer to the question put by KCNA on Monday as regards the Key Resolve and Foal Eagle joint military exercises launched by the U.S. and south Korea: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and the south Korean bellicose forces started the above-said military exercises throughout south Korea on March 2 despite the repeated warnings of the DPRK, thus rendering the situation on the Korean Peninsula to an extreme pitch of tension. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Involved there are the U.S. forces present in south Korea and  forces from its mainland and the south Korean forces and latest military hardware including the nuclear-powered ultra-large carrier Nimitz and nuclear-powered guided-missile submarine Ohio of the U.S. Navy. They are, to all intents and purposes, maneuvers for a nuclear war to seize the DPRK by force of arms in light of their scale and nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. kicked off the nuclear war maneuvers against its dialogue partner though it has talked about a "peaceful solution of the nuclear issue" and the "establishment of a peace-keeping mechanism on the Korean Peninsula." This is a clear indication that the U.S. is invariably sticking to its hostile policy to stifle the DPRK by force. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such nuclear threat and blackmail do not work on the DPRK but will only put a brake on the process of the denuclearization of the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK are following with the highest vigilance the military attempt of the U.S. to gravely threaten the sovereignty of the DPRK and take necessary countermeasures including those to further bolster up all its deterrent forces.

Stop to Joint War Exercises Targeted against DPRK Demanded 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The United States and the south Korean bellicose forces had better ponder over the catastrophic consequences to be entailed by their reckless moves to invade the north and stop at once their provocative joint war exercises against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland demanded this in a statement issued on March 2 assailing the U.S. and the south Korean military warmongers for launching the Key Resolve and Foal Eagle joint military exercises, large-scale war maneuvers targeted against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These war exercises the main purpose of which is to promptly hurl and deploy forces for invading the north into south Korea in case of "contingency" and escalate and conclude a war are very dangerous maneuvers for a preliminary war, a nuclear war targeted against the north as they are little different from the past Team Spirit and RSOI in their nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are arousing ever greater apprehension at home and abroad as they are to be staged under the simulated conditions of an actual war in a bid to develop the "CONPLAN 5029," a war scenario for invading the north, which has been pushed forward by the U.S. and the south Korean military warmongers in real earnest, into "OPLAN 5029," a scenario for mounting a surprise preemptive strike. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and south Korean war-like forces claim that the above-said exercises are of "defensive nature" but this is nothing but sophism which can convince no one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The warmongers' reckless moves for a war of aggression against the north are throwing a stumbling block in the way of settling the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. and developing the inter-Korean relations and creating a very grave situation which may bring back the atmosphere of reconciliation, unity, peace and reunification on the Korean Peninsula to the phase of confrontation and war any moment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality more clearly proves that the source of tensions and the danger of war on the Korean Peninsula have always come from the U.S. and south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dialogue and confrontation, and peace and war cannot go together. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that the U.S. and south Korean bellicose forces are persistently pursuing a war of aggression against the north, while brandishing a nuclear stick behind the scene of "dialogue," "peace" and "improved relations," the DPRK has no option but to take strong self-defensive measures for protecting the dignity and sovereignty of the country and nation and peace and stability on the peninsula.

Working People Plant Trees 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- Working people and school youth and children in all parts of the country have turned out in the spring tree-planting on the occasion of the tree-planting day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meetings of working people, school youth and children, agricultural workers and members of the women's union were held on Sunday across the country at which the participants resolved to energetically do the work to turn the country into a thick woodland and greenery true to the far-reaching idea of land development of General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meetings stressed the need to plant trees of good species on the principle of the right tree on the right soil and tend trees well, highly aware that tree-planting is a work for the prosperity of the country and the happiness of the generations to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Party and state officials participated in the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the meetings the participants planted with good care thousands of trees and flower shrubs including pine nut tree, maple tree, Evodia Daniellii Benn and Metasequoia in the arboretum of the Kumsusan Memorial Palace, the Munsubong Revolutionary Site and around the Three-Revolution Exhibition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Tree planting took place in all provinces, cities and counties on the same day.

Exceptional Winter Climate 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- An abnormal climatic phenomenon never seen previously was witnessed in the DPRK last winter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Mun Uk, a room chief in the Hydro-Meteorological Service, said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A temperature below fifteen degrees Celsius below zero was quite rare in the winter season and it passed without midwinter cold. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cycle of three cold days and four warm days which had occurred   with the periodic alternation of high and low atmospheric pressures was hardly witnessed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And there was a little snow with the dry weather prolonged. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to data available, snow scarcely fell in Pyongyang and other areas of the western coast and some areas of the eastern coast in the period from mid-December last year to February 21 this year and the precipitation in January was 0 mm in Pyongyang, Phyongsong and Sariwon, the lowest ever since the beginning of meteorological observation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sustained period without rain or snow was 67 days in Pyongyang and 59 days in Sariwon, which was a phenomenon rare to be seen. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the previous period, Korea had been influenced by the cold northwest seasonal wind with the development of the Siberian anticyclone in winter and by a migratory anticyclone and a traveling cyclone when it abated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But, last winter, a cold and dry weather continued with the sustained strengthening of the continental anticyclone which occurred in Huabei region of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This abnormal climatic phenomenon has seriously affected the growth of autumn wheat and barley.

New Scientific Films Released 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Korean Documentary and Scientific Film Studio has produced scientific films to help people get new know-how and common knowledge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film "Newly Discovered Enzyme Dissolving Fur-Protein" introduces an enzyme that will make a great contribution to the development of stock-breeding and fish farming. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The enzyme is used to convert fur of various kinds of animals, which had been dumped, into nutritious feeds for domestic animals and fishes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film shows interestingly how the enzyme is used in various economic sectors and families. It not only converts animal fur into protein fodder but also makes leather products softer and raises wash effect two times that by other methods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film "Jangajji, Folk Dishes" gives plenty of common sense on tasty jangajji, which has been created and developed by the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jangajji, essential foodstuff, is processed by the method of seasoning dried or pickled slices of vegetables and edible herbs with soy-sauce, bean paste or peppered bean paste. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film details the history of jangajji, scientific methods of making it and its good influence on health.

Japan's Diplomacy for Pressurizing DPRK under Fire  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries are busy with entreaty diplomacy towards different countries in a bid to make the United Nations adopt a resolution on the non-existent "north Korean human rights issue," while persistently crying out for the "solution of the abduction issue" which had already found a solution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Monday observes in a signed commentary carried in this regard: This is a cunning and sinister move peculiar to Japan and an anachronistic action to bar the six-party talks from making any progress, evade its responsibility for making reparation for its human rights abuse in the past and do harm to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is natural that these days dietmen from the Democratic Party of Japan are becoming increasingly critical of the government's "diplomacy solely aimed at pressurizing the DPRK." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their criticism and assertion can be interpreted as strong censure of the politically and diplomatically incompetent Japanese government as it is not in a position to judge the situation for the lack of political sense and insight and failed to observe elementary international practice and keep faith in the international relations in pursuit of its present interests. They are, at the same time, a warning against the consequences to be entailed by the government's hostile policy towards the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese government would be well advised to come to its senses though belatedly, not lending a deaf ear to the criticism made by lawmakers from the DPJ, and drop its wrong viewpoint and policy towards the DPRK. It is a political and diplomatic mistake and harmful for the Japanese government to stick to the above-said diplomacy toward the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan persists in its hostile policy towards the DPRK, talking nonsense, there will be no thaw in the DPRK-Japan relations now remaining frozen and it will be derided and rejected by the public for being a "political dwarf."

Display of Patriotism Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- All the people should work hard with ardent patriotism and thus proudly greet September marking the 60th anniversary of the DPRK with signal labour achievements and merits of creation, Rodong Sinmun says in an editorial article on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that patriotism is a great mental power for building a rich and powerful country, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To build a great prosperous powerful nation is a popular cause in which all the people loving the country should turn out, and the way for carrying out this cause is for all the people to become patriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people could go along the road of genuine patriotism for the country and nation when they held President Kim Il Sung in high esteem as father of the nation. And under the guidance of Kim Jong Il, a peerless patriot, there emerged the political and military power dignified for its strong independence and with the might of Songun and our generation has had a privilege to open the gate to a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We should surely glorify the Songun era steered by Kim Jong Il as the heyday of prosperity to be specially recorded in the history of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rare in the world is such nation as the Korean people enjoying much benefit from the state. Just today when one is blessed as much as one dedicates one's strength and wisdom, to display patriotism is a shortcut to creating happiness for oneself. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A patriot in the present times is immediately a hot-blooded person who devotedly safeguards Kim Jong Il while remaining true to the Songun leadership of the Party, a person of self-reliance creating happiness in reliance on his strength, and a true and faithful person reliably keeping his post with high degree of working spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article calls upon all the people to lead a worthwhile life as patriots in the Songun era in the course of providing the everlasting red glow of prosperity to the country under the leadership of Kim Jong Il.

All Koreans Called upon to Uphold Songun Politics 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea is the noblest patriotic politics as it helps reliably protect the dignity and sovereignty of the country and nation and achieve their prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun serves as an invincible treasured sword for remarkably increasing the national power and the might of the Koreans. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There have been not a few different political ideas and modes advocating patriotism in history. But the Songun politics of the WPK is the only genuine political mode as it most fully reflects the popular masses' desire and aspiration and helps most successfully achieve the independence of the country and nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But for the invincible military power built up under the banner of Songun, the U.S. imperialists would have forced a nuclear war upon the Korean nation long ago and the territory of Korea would have suffered from the thermonuclear war ignited by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is thanks to Songun that the Korean nation is demonstrating its dignity as a strong nation with tremendous military deterrent whom no formidable enemy dares attack. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Songun serves as a motive force instilling true patriotism into the members of the nation and encouraging them to fully display it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now that the U.S. imperialists are getting more undisguised in their moves to dominate the whole of Korea and its entire nation an attitude towards the Songun politics serves as a touchstone distinguishing patriotism from treachery, concludes the article.

Return of Nuclear-powered Carrier Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists' nuclear-powered aircraft carrier Nimitz anchored in a naval base in Pusan on February 28 to participate in the Key Resolve and Foal Eagle joint military exercises, according to a news report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korea-U.S. "Combined Forces Command" announced that the carrier would be deployed at the beginning of a war as it is to play a key role in "increasing combat capability" of the U.S. forces in case of "contingency." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this regard more than 100 civic and social organizations in Pusan called a joint press conference outside the Naval Operation Command there on the same day and bitterly denounced that the U.S. nuclear-powered warships of different missions have entered the base one after another since it was built. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations strongly demanded prompt return of the carrier, saying that ceaseless entry of the U.S. nuclear-powered warships precisely means its will to continue war games in disregard of the south Koreans' lives.

Security Authorities' Suppression Protested in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Youth and Students Solidarity for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration in south Korea reportedly made public a statement on February 28 in protest against the security authorities' arrest of Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the security authorities walked him off on Feb. 27 on the charge of violation of the "National Security Law" (NSL), the statement said that the recently successive suppression of pro-reunification patriotic forces obviously reveals the authorities' true colors as separatists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though the security authorities are seeking to brand all the people desirous of reunification as violators of the NSL, the independent reunification becomes the trend of the times and it is definite, it said, contending that any harsh repression can never block the advance of youth and students toward reunification.

S. Korean Security Authorities' Anti-Reunification Moves Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Overseas Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) made public a statement on March 1 denouncing the south Korean security authorities' recent arrest of Yun Ki Jin, chairman of the South Headquarters of Pomchonghakryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean security authorities have put many pro-reunification patriotic figures behind bars this year, the statement said, strongly urging them to immediately set free Yun Ki Jin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such suppression of patriotic youth aspiring after the national reunification has been made at the present time when all Koreans in the north and the south and abroad are advancing towards the new era of independent reunification, a new era of peace and prosperity, under the banner of "By our nation itself." This is an anti-national and fascist violence, an anachronistic move against reunification and a blatant challenge to the spirit of the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Overseas Headquarters of Pomchonghakryon will never pardon the south Korean security authorities' anachronistic anti-reunification deed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We strongly demand once again that they abrogate the "National Security Law," an evil law against the nation and reunification, and release all the detained pro-reunification patriots.

April Spring Friendship Art Festival Introduced in Romania
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 3 (KCNA) -- The Romanian Ministry of Culture and Religion introduced through its Internet homepage the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival on Feb. 26. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In its makeup titled "The DPRK-Pyongyang April Spring Friendship Art Festival" the homepage carried pictures showing the opening and closing and awarding ceremonies of the festival, performances of Korean and Romanian artistes and scenes of the grand gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival held in Pyongyang on the occasion of the Day of the Sun was very excellent in its scale and form, the homepage said, elaborating on the fact that the Romanian music troupe participated in the festival and the members of the troupe appreciated the performance "Arirang" with deep emotion.

Declara portavoz de representacion del EPC en Phanmunjom 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 3 de marzo (ATCC) -- En relacion con que Estados Unidos y los belicistas surcoreanos iniciaron el dia 2 en toda la extension surcoreana los ejercicios militares conjuntos "Key Resolve" y "Aguilucho" suponiendo la segunda guerra coreana, el portavoz de la Representacion del Ejercito Popular de Corea (EPC) en Phanmunjom hizo publica la vispera una declaracion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Este simulacro conjunto Sur de Corea-EE.UU. que se libra con el nuevo rotulo "Key Resolve" en vez del anterior "ejercicio conjunto de refuerzo para el tiempo de guerra" es el ejercicio belico para aplastar con las fuerzas armadas la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea llevando al "triunfo" la guerra mediante el "despliegue eficiente de las tropas norteamericanas de refuerzo en el 'tiempo de emergencia'", dijo el portavoz y prosiguio: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  EE.UU. ubica el aparato de mando de agresion sobre el terreno en la Peninsula Coreana y su contorno y refuerza en gran medida las fuerzas aereas para desarrollar los freneticos ejercicios belicos junto con las fuerzas belicistas del Sur de Corea, lo cual demuestra que el imperio prueba y revisa realmente el nuevo metodo de guerra de lanzar las  fuerzas terrestres luego de reducir a cenizas la RPDC al inicio de la guerra por el golpe preventivo aereo incluido el nuclear. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Ahora, las fuerzas conservadoras intransigentes de EE.UU. y el Sur de Corea hablan de que "el Norte de Corea infringio el tiempo de la ejecucion del Acuerdo del 3 de Octubre" y "es necesario tomar nuevas medidas si el Norte de Corea sigue aplazando la declaracion nuclear". Coincidiendo con estos disparates la capa militar norteamericana aumenta armamentos y libra con frenesi los ejercicios belicos, lo que deviene un abierto desafio a la desnuclearizacion y la paz de la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Todos los hechos demuestran claramente que EE.UU. no tiene ni en lo minimo la idea de renunciar su politica hostil a Corea y que el "dialogo", el "fin del armisticio" y la "desnuclearizacion de la Peninsula Coreana", de que los yanquis hablan tanto, no pasan de ser una farsa astuta para encubrir su preparacion de guerra nuclear, desarmarnos y enganar la opinion publica del mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El ejercito coreano no esperaba beneficios algunos que emanen del dialogo con EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Si EE.UU. y las fuerzas belicistas del Sur de Corea tratan de llevar a efecto su intento de aplastarnos militarmente, el EPC les respondera no con la defensa pasiva sino con el iniciativo golpe de disposicion movilizando todos los medios preparados costosamente durante largo tiempo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
EE.UU. y sus perseguidores asumiran la entera responsabilidad de todas las consecuencias que emanen de ello.

CRPP demanda el cese de ejercicios belicos contra la RPDC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 3 de marzo (ATCC) -- Estados Unidos y las fuerzas belicistas del Sur de Corea deben reflexionar seriamente de las consecuencias destructivas de sus frivolas maniobras de agresion al Norte de Corea y parar ahora mismo los provocativos ejercicios belicos conjuntos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senalo el portavoz del Comite por la Reunificacion Pacifica de la Patria (CRPP) en su declaracion publicada el dia 2 en relacion con que EE.UU. y los belicistas de la capa militar del Sur de Corea iniciaron por fin los agresivos ejercicios militares conjuntos de gran envergadura "Key Resolve" y "Aguilucho".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Estos simulacros tienen como su objetivo principal lanzar y desplegar rapido en el suelo surcoreano a las fuerzas armadas agresoras al Norte de Corea en los "tiempos de emergencia" y finalizar la guerra tras ampliarla de manera escalonada. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Por lo tanto, esas guerras preliminares sumamente peligrosas para ejercitar el ataque nuclear contra el Norte de Corea son identicas a las maniobras anteriores "Team Spirit" o "ejercicios combinados de refuerzo para el tiempo de guerra".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En particular, esos ejercicios militares causan gran preocupacion en el interior y el exterior del pais porque se encaminan a completar el "plan conceptual 5029", guion de guerra contra el Norte de Corea de EE.UU. y los belicistas de la capa militar surcoreana, como el "plan operacional 5029", que aboga por el ataque preventivo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque ellos hablan mucho del caracter "defensivo" de esos simulacros, esta farsa no podra convencer a nadie. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Debido al imprudente procedimiento de esos belicistas, se obstaculizan seriamente la solucion del problema nuclear entre la RPDC y EE.UU. y el desarrollo de las relaciones entre el Norte y el Sur de Corea. Tambien se produce una situacion tan grave en que el clima por la reconciliacion, la unidad, la paz y la reunificacion de la Peninsula Coreana puede caer en cualquier momento en la coyuntura de confrontacion y guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La realidad comprueba con mas claridad que tanto ayer como hoy, EE.UU. y el Sur de Corea son factores de la agravacion de la tension y del peligro de guerra en la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El dialogo y la paz son incompatibles con la confrontacion y la guerra. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Dado que EE.UU. y las fuerzas belicistas surcoreanas se obstinan en la guerra de agresion al Norte de Corea esgrimiendo el garrote nuclear detras de la cortina del "dialogo", la "paz" y la "mejora de las relaciones", tomaremos resueltamente contramedidas de autodefensa para salvaguardar la dignidad y la soberania del pais y la nacion y preservar la paz y la estabilidad de l

EE.UU. y ejercito surcoreano comienzan ejercicios militares
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 3 de marzo (ATCC) -- Segun fuentes militares, las tropas agresoras norteamericanas y el ejercito surcoreano iniciaron el dia 2 por fin los ejercicios militares conjuntos "Key Resolve" y "Aguilucho" de caracter agresivo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mas de 12 mil efectivos ocupantes del Sur de Corea entraron en la disposicion de combate, mientras mas de 6 mil provenientes de base ultramarina fueron desplegados en las bases avanzadas del Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Entretanto, otros mas de 9 mil uniformados norteamericanos estan esperando ordenes en el mar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Arribaron el 28 de febrero al puerto de Pusan el portaaviones de propulsion nuclear de tamano supergrande "Nimitz", el dia 20 el submarino nuclear "Ohio" cargado de mas de 150 misiles cruceros "Tomahawk" y el dia primero un buque de desembarco. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Por otra parte, llego el 26 de febrero al puerto de Jinhae un carguero repleto de los equipos del cuerpo de marines. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Coincidiendo con la aparicion de "Nimitz" en el puerto de Pusan, llegaron al puerto de Phyongthaek dos destructores con misiles teledirigidos y al puerto de Tonghae, los buques del mismo tipo "Chaffee" y "John S. McCain".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Igualmente, se trasladaron a la base aerea de Osan y al aeropuerto de Kunsan del Sur de Corea los cazabombarderos "F-15" y "F-16", el avion de asalto "F/A-18", el avion de operacion especial "MC-130" y el avion nodriza "KC-135" procedentes de las bases en el territorio norteamericano y en ultramar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Mientras tanto, estan dispuestas a sumarse a esos simulacros las fuerzas navales y aereas de EE.UU. desplegadas en las aguas maritimas y zonas aledanas a la Peninsula Coreana incluidos Japon y la isla Guam. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aparte de esas colosales fuerzas armadas de EE.UU., entraron junto con la alarma de emergencia en la disposicion de combate las fuerzas terrestres, navales y aereas, el cuerpo de marines, el "Ejercito de Reserva Local", la policia, los organismos administrativos, los principales complejos belicos y civiles del Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
A traves de los ejercicios militares "Key Resolve" y "Aguilucho", las tropas norteamericanas y el ejercito surcoreano pretenden ejercitar para la eventual guerra coreana el desplazamiento, el despliegue, la formacion de las unidades combinadas y las operaciones de tropas especiales en el Norte de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Debido a esas desenfrenadas maniobras belicas, en la Peninsula Coreana se da una situacion extremadamente peligrosa.
